HEADWORD: Gastræa
<hw>Gas*tr⟦ae⟧"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/, <?/, the stomach.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A primeval
larval form; a double-walled sac from which, according to the hypothesis
of Haeckel, man and all other animals, that in the first stages of their
individual evolution pass through a two-layered structural stage, or
gastrula form, must have descended. This idea constitutes the
<xex>Gastr⟦ae⟧a theory</xex> of Haeckel. See
<er>Gastrula</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gastralgia</ent>⟦br⟧
